# Frontend Rules — Scaler App

## Next.js App Router

- **App Router only** — no Pages Router
- **Server Components by default** — use `'use client'` only when required:
  - Event handlers (onClick, onChange, onSubmit)
  - React hooks (useState, useEffect, useContext)
  - Browser-only APIs (localStorage, window, navigator)
  - TanStack Query hooks
  - Framer Motion animations
- Layout hierarchy: root layout → route group layouts → page-specific layouts

## Route Groups

### `(unauthorised)` — Public / Unauthenticated Pages
Pages accessible **without login**. No auth middleware applied.
```
App/src/app/(unauthorised)/
├── login/page.tsx              # Login form
├── signup/page.tsx             # Registration form
├── [username]/                 # Public user profile
│   └── [slug]/page.tsx         # Public booking page (calendar + slots + form)
├── booking/
│   ├── confirmed/page.tsx      # Booking success page
│   └── [id]/
│       ├── cancel/page.tsx     # Cancel booking flow
│       └── reschedule/page.tsx # Reschedule booking flow
└── layout.tsx                  # Minimal layout (no sidebar, no auth check)
```

### `(authorised)` — Protected / Authenticated Pages
Pages requiring **active session**. Layout includes auth guard + sidebar navigation.
All API calls are secured with JWT. Redirect to login if unauthenticated.
```
App/src/app/(authorised)/
├── event-types/
│   ├── page.tsx                # Event type list (card grid)
│   ├── new/page.tsx            # Create new event type
│   └── [id]/page.tsx           # Edit event type (multi-tab form + preview)
├── bookings/
│   └── page.tsx                # Bookings dashboard (tabs: Upcoming, Past, Cancelled)
├── availability/
│   ├── page.tsx                # Schedule list
│   └── [id]/page.tsx           # Edit schedule (day toggles + time ranges + overrides)
├── apps/
│   ├── page.tsx                # Installed apps
│   └── store/page.tsx          # App store (browse + install integrations)
├── settings/
│   ├── page.tsx                # Settings overview grid
│   ├── profile/page.tsx        # Profile editing
│   ├── general/page.tsx        # Language, timezone, time format
│   ├── appearance/page.tsx     # Theme selection (System/Light/Dark)
│   └── calendars/page.tsx      # Connected calendar accounts
└── layout.tsx                  # Auth guard + sidebar + top bar
```

## API Communication

- All API calls go through `lib/api.ts` (typed fetch wrapper)
- The API client:
  - Adds Authorization header automatically from auth store
  - Handles token refresh on 401 responses
  - Parses responses into `ApiResponse<T>` type
  - Base URL from `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` env var
- **No direct `fetch()` calls in components** — always use TanStack Query hooks

## Data Fetching Pattern

```typescript
// hooks/use-event-types.ts
import { useQuery, useMutation, useQueryClient } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { api } from '@/lib/api';

export function useEventTypes() {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['event-types'],
    queryFn: () => api.get<EventType[]>('/event-types'),
  });
}

export function useCreateEventType() {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: (data: CreateEventTypeInput) => api.post<EventType>('/event-types', data),
    onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['event-types'] }),
  });
}
```

## Form Handling

- All forms use **React Hook Form** + `zodResolver`
- Zod schemas shared between frontend validation and backend (via shared types)
- Pattern:
  ```typescript
  const form = useForm<CreateEventTypeInput>({
    resolver: zodResolver(createEventTypeSchema),
    defaultValues: { ... },
  });
  ```

## UI Components

- **shadcn/ui** for all UI primitives — do not build buttons, inputs, dialogs, dropdowns, etc. from scratch
- Components installed via `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`
- shadcn components live in `components/ui/`
- Custom composite components in `components/` (e.g., `sidebar.tsx`, `booking-card.tsx`)

## Styling Rules

- **Tailwind CSS only** — no inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Use `cn()` utility (from shadcn) for conditional class merging
- Color system: use Tailwind's neutral palette for dark theme, brand colors via CSS variables
- Responsive design: mobile-first approach with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints

## Theme System

- User-configurable theme (light/dark mode)
- Default: dark mode (matching Cal.com screenshots)
- Implementation: `next-themes` for theme switching
- CSS variables define color tokens, toggled by `dark` class on `<html>`
- Theme toggle available in sidebar/settings

## Animation Rules

- **Framer Motion** for:
  - Page transitions (fade/slide between routes)
  - Modal/dialog open/close animations
  - List item enter/exit animations
  - Micro-interactions (button hover, card hover)
- Keep animations subtle and fast (150-300ms)
- Use `AnimatePresence` for exit animations
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` media query

## Auth Flow (Frontend)

- Auth state managed in Zustand store (`stores/auth-store.ts`)
- On app load: check for existing refresh token cookie → auto-login
- If no session: auto-login with default credentials (bypass mode for assignment)
- Access token stored in memory (Zustand), refresh token in httpOnly cookie
- API client intercepts 401 → attempts token refresh → retries original request
- `(authorised)` layout checks auth state → redirects to `/login` if not authenticated
- `(unauthorised)` layout checks auth state → redirects to `/event-types` if already logged in

## File Naming

- Components: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g., `booking-card.tsx`, `time-slot-picker.tsx`)
- Query hooks: `hooks/queries/use-{name}.ts` (e.g., `use-event-types.ts`)
- Mutation hooks: `hooks/mutations/use-{name}.ts` (e.g., `use-create-booking.ts`)
- Stores: `stores/{name}-store.ts` (e.g., `auth-store.ts`)
- Types: `types/{name}.types.ts` or inline in the file
- Pages: `page.tsx` (Next.js convention)
- Layouts: `layout.tsx` (Next.js convention)
- Error pages: `error.tsx` (Next.js convention — required in every route segment)
- Loading pages: `loading.tsx` (Next.js convention — required in every route segment)

