- **Atomic components** (`ui/`): shadcn-managed only — never edit manually
- **Feature components** (`[feature]/`): contain feature-specific rendering logic
- **Layout components** (`layout/`): structural shell — never mix feature logic into layout
- **Shared components** (`shared/`): generic reusable patterns (error boundaries, empty states)

## Props Rules

- All component props defined as a TypeScript `interface`, never inline
- All prop interfaces named `[ComponentName]Props`
- Required props first, optional props last
- No prop drilling beyond 2 levels — use context or Zustand beyond that
- No passing entire objects when only one field is needed — pass the field
- Callback props named `on[Event]`: `onBookingCancel`, `onSlotSelect`, `onToggleActive`

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
interface BookingCardProps {
  title: string;           // required first
  startTime: string;
  endTime: string;
  status: BookingStatus;
  onCancel: (id: string) => void;
  meetingUrl?: string;     // optional last
  className?: string;
}

// ❌ Wrong: inline props, entire object, wrong naming
function BookingCard({ booking, cancel }: { booking: Booking; cancel: () => void }) {}
```

## Error Boundaries

- Every route segment must be wrapped in an Error Boundary.
- Create a reusable `<ErrorBoundary>` component that accepts a `fallback` render prop.
- Create a `<RouteErrorBoundary>` that wraps each page and shows a styled error UI matching Cal.com's design.
- Never let an uncaught render error crash the entire app.
- In Next.js App Router: every route segment directory must have an `error.tsx` file.
- Every async Server Component must have a corresponding `error.tsx` sibling.
- Log all caught errors to the logger with component stack trace.

## Suspense & Loading States

- Every async data fetch must have a Suspense boundary with a skeleton fallback.
- Never show a blank screen while data loads. Always show a skeleton that matches the shape of the loaded UI.
- Create skeleton components for: BookingCardSkeleton, EventTypeCardSkeleton, TimeSlotSkeleton, CalendarSkeleton.
- In Next.js App Router: every route segment directory must have a `loading.tsx` file.
- Use `<Suspense>` boundaries at the component level, not just the page level.
- Streaming: use Next.js streaming for the public booking page — stream the calendar shell immediately, stream time slots after.

## TanStack Query Rules

- Every API call is a TanStack Query hook. No raw fetch in components.
- Query keys are defined as typed constants in lib/constants.ts (e.g. `QUERY_KEYS.EVENT_TYPES`). Never inline string query keys.
- All query hooks live in hooks/queries/. All mutation hooks live in hooks/mutations/.
- Every mutation hook implements:
  - onSuccess: invalidate affected query keys
  - onError: show toast notification with typed error message
  - optimistic update where appropriate (booking cancel, event type toggle)
- Retry logic: queries retry 2 times on network errors, 0 times on 4xx errors.
- Stale time: 30 seconds for most data, 0 for bookings (always fresh), 5 minutes for public event type data.
- Error handling: extract error message from ApiResponse envelope in a shared queryClient error handler.

## API Client Rules

- Single typed API client in `lib/api.ts`.
- All methods are typed: `get<T>`, `post<T>`, `put<T>`, `patch<T>`, `delete<T>`.
- All methods parse response as `ApiResponse<T>` and throw typed `ApiError` on non-2xx.
- Automatic retry: 2 retries with exponential backoff (1s, 2s) for network errors only.
- Automatic token refresh: intercept 401, refresh token, replay original request once.
- If refresh fails, clear auth state and redirect to login.
- Request deduplication: identical in-flight GET requests are deduplicated.

## Debounce Rules

- Any input that triggers an API call must be debounced. Minimum 300ms.
- Slug uniqueness check on event type creation form: debounced 500ms.
- Search inputs: debounced 300ms.
- Use a single `useDebounce` hook from `hooks/use-debounce.ts`. Never inline debounce logic.
- Never use setTimeout for debouncing in components. Use the hook.

## Pagination Rules

- Every list view uses cursor-based pagination, not offset pagination.
- Backend returns `{ data: T[], nextCursor: string | null, hasMore: boolean }`.
- Frontend uses TanStack Query `useInfiniteQuery` for infinite scroll lists.
- Bookings list: infinite scroll with intersection observer. Load more when last card enters viewport.
- Event types list: standard paginated (not infinite) because the list is short and managed.
- Create a reusable `usePaginatedList` hook that handles cursor, loading state, and intersection observer.
- Never load all records at once. Page size: 20 for bookings, 50 for time slots.

## Performance Rules

- `React.memo` on all presentational components that receive stable props.
- `useMemo` for expensive derived data (available time slots calculation, filtered booking lists).
- `useCallback` for all callback props passed to memoized children.
- Dynamic imports (`next/dynamic`) for: date picker, rich text editor, any component > 50kb.
- Images: always use `next/image`. Never raw `<img>`.
- Fonts: `next/font` only. Never link tag fonts.
- Bundle: analyze with `@next/bundle-analyzer` before any release. No bundle > 200kb initial JS.
- Virtualization: use `@tanstack/react-virtual` for any list that can exceed 50 items.
- No layout shift: all dynamic content areas have explicit height/min-height set.

## Reusable Component Checklist

Before building any component, ask:
1. Does this already exist in shadcn/ui? If yes, use it.
2. Does a similar component already exist in this codebase? If yes, extend it.
3. Is this component generic enough to be reused in 2+ places? If yes, put it in components/ui/.
4. Does this component mix data-fetching with rendering? If yes, split it.

## Consistency Rules

- All date/time display uses a single `formatDate` utility from `lib/format.ts`. Never use `toLocaleDateString()` directly in components.
- All currency display uses a single `formatCurrency` utility.
- All error messages come from a central `error-messages.ts` constants file. Never hardcode error strings in components.
- All route paths come from `lib/constants.ts` constants. Never hardcode route strings.
- All API endpoint paths come from `lib/constants.ts` constants. Never hardcode URL strings.
- Toast notifications use a single `useToast` hook. Never call `toast()` directly in components.

